U.K. stocks declined, after the
benchmark FTSE 100 Index posted four successive weeks of gains,
GlaxoSmithKline Plc and Vodafone Group Plc retreated.  The FTSE 100 slipped 13.83 points, or 0.2 percent, to
6,616.84 at 8:29 a.m. in  London . The gauge has jumped 9.8
percent since June 24 as central banks around the world promised
to continue to support economic recovery. The FTSE All-Share
Index also lost 0.2 percent today, while Irelandâ€™s ISEQ Index
